---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <section class="px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto flex w-full max-w-4xl flex-col gap-10">
      <header class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-primary/60 dark:text-white/60">Writing Studio</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary dark:text-white sm:text-5xl">
          Mako Writer
        </h1>
        <p class="max-w-3xl text-base text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 sm:text-lg">
          AI book-writing studio for fiction and non-fiction teams. Plan faster, draft cleaner, and ship manuscripts
          with a workflow that feels like a focused product, not a pile of disconnected tools.
        </p>
      </header>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-primary/10 bg-white/80 p-8 shadow-lg shadow-primary/5 dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-secondary/60">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary dark:text-white">What makes it different</h2>
        <ul class="mt-5 space-y-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 sm:text-base">
          <li>• Built for long-form writing, with project-level structure for chapters, arcs, and revisions.</li>
          <li>• AI assistant that works inside your manuscript context for drafting, rewriting, and expansion.</li>
          <li>• Professional export path for deliverables and publishing-ready document workflows.</li>
          <li>• Dedicated writing, planning, and preview modes so flow and editing stay separated and clean.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-primary/10 bg-white/80 p-8 shadow-lg shadow-primary/5 dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-secondary/60">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary dark:text-white">Who it is for</h2>
        <ul class="mt-5 space-y-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 sm:text-base">
          <li>• Fiction authors building novels, series, and story-driven worlds.</li>
          <li>• Non-fiction teams creating books, educational titles, and research-backed content.</li>
          <li>• Creators replacing scattered notes and chat tabs with one production-ready writing stack.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-primary/10 bg-white/80 p-8 shadow-lg shadow-primary/5 dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-secondary/60">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary dark:text-white">Stack</h2>
        <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {["Tauri", "React", "TypeScript", "Zustand", "CodeMirror", "Paged.js"].map((stack) => (
            <span class="rounded-full border border-primary/10 px-4 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-primary/70 dark:border-white/15 dark:text-white/70">
              {stack}
            </span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-primary/10 bg-white/80 p-8 shadow-lg shadow-primary/5 dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-secondary/60">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary dark:text-white">Product direction</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 sm:text-base">
          Mako Writer is evolving into a complete writing pipeline: idea capture, structure planning, AI-assisted
          drafting, and final export in one desktop environment. The goal is simple: less tool-juggling, more finished books.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
